<TITLE> Bill placed to raise retirement age of FF civil servants </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 27 (bdnews24.com)--The government has introduced a bill in parliament to change the law to increase the retirement age of civil servants who were freedom fighters. Agriculture minister Matia Chowdhury, in absence of local government minister Syed Ashraful Islam, tabled the bill which would hike the retirement age to 59 from 57. The Public Servants (Retirement) (Amendment) Bill-2010 was sent to the parliamentary standing committee on establishment ministry for further scrutiny. The bill proposes that the public freedom-fighter servants, who went to leave preparatory to retirement (LPR) just before introduction of the new section of the bill, will be re-appointed. President Zillur Rahman on Dec 13 last year promulgated an ordinance to increase the retirement age of the freedom fighter civil servants. Earlier, the cabinet approved the bill for passage in parliament
